timeline.bodyText:
So you overrode equals to get the effect of old.pageId==new.pageId here by converting them to strings first. Couple problems

Quite surprising, could have effects at any other comparison site
Android studio will create hashCode, equals & toString methods for you, press alt+insert
no hashcode implementation was added

To make explicit your intention you could have said
            @Override
            public boolean areContentsTheSame(Contribution oldConcert,
                Contribution newConcert) {
                return areItemsTheSame(oldConcert, newConcert);

which is I think what the intention was.
This leads in to the larger problem of a contribution can't change its contents which they should be able to do I think? This could lead to some very confusing errors where the data has been updated and it just won't render

